![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/60c692dc-d9bc-4592-bbb6-98c134b94042_1648868037.2552137.png)

We have 2 edge cases
**1st edge case**
if the first char is a ".', i.e dominoes[i] == '.', then its either :
All the '.' becomes 'L' **if our second pointer is 'L'**
**or**
All the '.' remain as '.' **if our second pointer is 'R'**
i.e. lets say we have dominoes = '.....L'
result = 'LLLLLL'
**or**
i.e. lets say we have dominoes= '.....R'
result = '.....R'

**2nd edge case**
if the last char is a ".', i.e dominoes[len(arr)-1] == '.', then its either :
All the '.' becomes 'R' **if our second pointer is 'R'**
**or**
All the '.' remain as '.' **if our second pointer is 'L'**
i.e. lets say we have dominoes = 'R.....'
result = 'RRRRRR'
**or**
i.e. lets say we have dominoes= 'L.....'
result = 'L.....'

Now that the 2 edge cases are handled, it is **guaranteed** that our pointer will start and end with either an 'L' or 'R'
With that, there are another **4 more possibilities of arrangements** which are **RR, LL, RL, LR**
**1st arragement : RR**
-All elements within RR will become 'R'
i.e. dominoes = "R.....R"
result = "RRRRRR"
**2nd arragement : LL**
-All elements within LL will become 'L'
i.e. dominoes = "L.....L"
result = "LLLLLL"
**3rd arragement : RL**
-half of the elements within RL will become 'R', another half will become 'L'
however, there are **2 cases to handle within this subproblem**, if we have **even** number of '.' within RL
i.e dominoes = "R....L"
result = "RRRLLL"
else, if we have **odd** number of '.' within RL
i.e. dominoes = "R.....L"
result = "RRR.LLL" (the midpoint should remain as a '.')
**4th arragement : LR**
No change within the elements of LR
i.e. dominoes = "L.....R"
result = "L.....R"

**C++**

	class Solution {
	public:
		string pushDominoes(string dominoes) {
			vector<char> arr(dominoes.begin(), dominoes.end());
			int low = 0, high = arr.size()-1;

			if (arr[low] == '.'){
				for (int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++){
					if (arr[i] == 'R'){
						low = i;
						break;
					}

					if (arr[i] == 'L'){
						for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) arr[j] = 'L';
						break;
					}      
				}
			}
			if (arr[high] == '.')
				for (int i = arr.size()-1; i > -1; i--){
					if (arr[i] == 'L'){
						high = i;
						break;
					}
					if (arr[i] == 'R'){
						for (int j=i; j<arr.size();j++) arr[j] = 'R';
						break;
					}
				}

			int i = low;
			for (int j = low+1; j<high+1; j++){
				if (arr[i] == 'R' && arr[j] == 'L'){
					int mid = (i+j)/2;
					int temp = j;
					while (i != j){
						if (i >= temp){
							i = j;
							break;
						}
						arr[i] = 'R';
						arr[temp] = 'L';

						temp--;
						i++;   
					}
				}
				if (arr[i] == 'R' && arr[j] == 'R'){
					while (i != j){
						arr[i] = 'R';
						i++;
					}
				}
				if (arr[i] == 'L' && arr[j] == 'L'){
					while (i != j){
						arr[i] = 'L';
						i++;
					}
				}
				if (arr[i] == 'L' && arr[j] == 'R') i = j;

			}

			string result = "";

			for (int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++) result += arr[i];

			return result;
		}
	};

