The idea here is to use two pointer approach.
We need to insert 'L' in the beginning to make the process easier.
initially i is pointing to beginning 'L'. 
j = i+1, continue incrementing j as long as dominoes[i]='.' 
As soon we encounter 'L' or 'R', we stop.
Here are 4 possibilities:
1. i='L' and j='L' --> we fill all the characters between i and j with 'L'
2. i='R' and j='R' --> we fill all the characters between i and j with 'R'.
3. i='L' and j='R' --> we don't do anything. All characters remain as it is.
4. i='R' and j='L' --> Here we need to fill the characters with 'R' and 'L' both. We calculate mid point between j-1 and i index and fill the characters as shown below.

Lastly, if j==size, that means we reached end, then check if dominoes[i]=='R' --> fill all characters till end with 'R'.
Adjust pointers i and j. We already processed characters till j. so now i=j.
