solutions.content:
We simulate falling dominos turn-by-turn. We need a copy of the string (```s```) to make modifications so all dominos are pushed "simultaneously". At the end of each turn, we return the result if there are no more changes (```s == ds```).

Each turn we run through all dominos. The ```if``` statement checks if the previous (```i - 1``` for L) or next (```i + 1``` for R) domino can be pushed: it's standing and there is no domino before/after it pushing in the opposite direction.
```
string pushDominoes(string ds) {
  for (string s = ds; ; s = ds) {
    for (auto i = 0, d = s[i] == 'L' ? -1 : 1; i < s.size(); d = s[++i] == 'L' ? -1 : 1)
      if (s[i] != '.' && i + d >= 0 && i + d < s.size() && s[i + d] == '.' &&
        (i + d * 2 < 0 || i + d * 2 >= s.size() || s[i + d * 2] != (s[i] == 'L' ? 'R' : 'L'))) ds[i + d] = s[i];
    if (s == ds) return s;
  }
}
```

