solutions.content:
Maintain two pointers **start** and **end**, and there are four cases:
**1. start = 'L' & end = 'R':** 
* In this case, the dominoes in between these will not fall
* Ex: **L....R** , ans = **L....R**

**2. start = 'R' & end = 'L'**
* In this case, the dominoes in between will fall in such a way that:
	* Dominoes near 'R' will fall toward right
	* Dominoes near 'L' will fall toward left
	* If there is a middle domino, it doesn't fall as the forces are balanced
	* Ex1: **R..L**, ans = **RRLL**
	* Ex2: **R...L**, ans = **RR.LL**

**3. start = 'L & end = 'L'**
* In this case, all the dominoes in between will fall toward left, due to the force from end domino
* Ex: **L...L**, ans = **LLLLL**

**4. start = 'R' & end = 'R'**
* In this case, all the dominoes in between will fall toward right, due to the force from start domino
* Ex: **R...R**, ans = **RRRRR**

**Note:** Consider there is a 'L' domino in the beginning and a 'R' domino in the ending (adding these will not affect the answer, and it is easy for maintaining pointers. Take a few examples and you'll understand this)

```
class Solution {
public:
    string pushDominoes(string dominoes) {
		// Adding a domino at the end
        dominoes.push_back('R');

		// Consider, there is a 'L' domino at the begin
        int startInd = -1;
        char start = 'L';

        for(int i=0; i<dominoes.size(); i++){
            int endInd = i;
            char end = dominoes[i];

            if(end == '.'){
                continue;
            }

            if(start == 'L' && end == 'R'){
                // Do nothing
            }
            else if(start == 'R' && end == 'L'){
                int len = endInd-startInd+1;
                int l = startInd+1, r = endInd-1;
                while(l<=r){
					// Middle domino
                    if(l == r){
                        dominoes[l++] = '.';
                    }
                    else{
                        dominoes[l++] = 'R';
                        dominoes[r--] = 'L';
                    }
                }
            }
            else if(start == 'L' && end == 'L'){
                int ind = endInd-1;
                while(ind > startInd){
                    dominoes[ind--] = 'L';
                }
            }
            else{
                int ind = startInd+1;
                while(ind < endInd){
                    dominoes[ind++] = 'R';
                }
            }
            start = end;
            startInd = endInd;
        }

		// Removing the domino added at the end
        dominoes.pop_back();
        return dominoes;
    }
};
