solutions.content:
**Idea**
Final state of a domino depends upon the time of `left` and `right` force applied on it.
* if time of left force <time of right force, then state of that domino will be `L`
* if time of left force >time of right force, then state of that domino will be `R`
* if time of left force = time of right force **(balanced state)**, then state of that domino will be `.`

This can be done using bfs.
**Time complexity**: O(n) , **Space complexity**: O(n)
```
class Solution {
public:
    string pushDominoes(string s) {
        vector<bool> vis(s.size(),0); // to track the processed indices
        vector<int> left(s.size(),INT_MAX);  // to store time of left force on index i
        vector<int> right(s.size(),INT_MAX);  // to store time of right force on index i
        queue<int> q;  // to store the under process indices

        for(int i = 0; i<s.size();++i){  // initialize all the initial state of
            if(s[i]=='L'){               //  left and right with time 0
               q.push(i); vis[i] = 1; left[i] = 0;
            }
            if(s[i]=='R'){
               q.push(i); vis[i] = 1; right[i] = 0;
            }
        }

        while(!q.empty()){
            int t = q.size();
            while(t--){
                int i = q.front(); q.pop();
                if(left[i]<right[i]){
                    s[i]='L'; 
                    if(i-1>=0){  // state 'L' will always push its previous index to left
